      "span_text": "C-terminally truncated ␣S (⌬C10: residues 1-130, ⌬C20: residues 1-120, and ⌬C30: residues 1-110) and N-terminally truncated ␣S (⌬N10: residues 11-140, ⌬N20: residues 21-140, and ⌬N30: residues 31-140) were amplified by PCR with the following primers and subcloned into pRK172 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] : ⌬C10, forward, 5Ј-aggagatatacatatggatgtattcatgaa-3Ј and reverse, 5Јatcggaattcaagcttttactcataaggcatttcat-3Ј; ⌬C20, forward, 5Ј-aggagatatacatatggatgtattcatgaa-3Ј and reverse, 5Ј-atcggaattcaagcttttactcataaggcatttcat-3Ј; ⌬C30, forward, 5Ј-aggagatatacatatggatgtattcatgaa-3Ј and reverse, 5Ј-atcggaattcaagcttttactcataaggcatttcat-3Ј; ⌬N10, forward, 5Ј-aggagatatacatatggccaaggagggagttgt-3Ј and reverse, 5Ј-atcggaattcaagcttttaggcttcaggttcgt-3Ј; ⌬N20, forward, 5Ј-aggagatatacatatgaaaaccaaacagggtgt-3Ј and reverse, 5Ј-atcggaattcaagcttttaggcttcaggttcgt-3Ј; ⌬N30, forward, 5Ј-aggagatatacatatgggaaagacaaaagaggg-3Ј and reverse, 5Ј-atcggaattcaagcttttaggcttcaggttcgt-3Ј."
